# Fluff Date: 2026-02-21 18:07:19
overview:<p>The Mist Lynx is a 25-ton Clan OmniMech designed by Clan Smoke Jaguar in 2926 to serve as a fast, agile light scout and raider. Designated "Koshi," meaning "small death," by Draconis Combine forces who first encountered the design during Operation REVIVAL, the Mist Lynx quickly earned a reputation for punishing enemies who underestimated its capabilities. The design proved so successful that it spread through Trials of Possession to the touman of every Clan within a generation of its introduction, becoming one of the most ubiquitous light OmniMechs in Clan service.</p><p>Despite its age and the introduction of newer light OmniMechs, the fundamental soundness of the Mist Lynx has kept it in continuous production across multiple Clan manufacturers for over a century. Its unmatched combination of speed, jump capability, and electronic warfare potential ensures that the design remains a valued asset in any Clan touman.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Mist Lynx is built on a lightweight Light Series II endo steel chassis powered by a Type II 175 XL engine, propelling the twenty-five-ton OmniMech to speeds approaching 119 kilometers per hour. Six jump jets provide an impressive 180-meter jump capability, granting the design exceptional tactical flexibility across varied terrain. Only the Grendel and Dragonfly among standard OmniMech configurations can match this combination of speed and agility. A permanently mounted active probe allows the Mist Lynx to detect hidden units before they can spring an ambush, making it a natural choice for reconnaissance operations and screening duties.</p><p>This fixed equipment, combined with the endo steel frame and ferro-fibrous armor, comes at a significant cost to offensive capability. The Mist Lynx has only seven and a half tons of available pod space, among the lowest of any Clan OmniMech. Armor protection is particularly thin at just three and a half tons of Compound H17 ferro-fibrous plating, making the design extremely vulnerable to concentrated fire. In its Prime configuration, the 'Mech carries an LRM-10 for ranged engagement, a Streak SRM-4 for close combat, and a pair of machine guns for anti-infantry work. The Mist Lynx's true strength lies not in any single weapons loadout but in its nearly unmatched maneuverability, which allows skilled MechWarriors to dictate engagement terms against heavier opponents.</p>

deployment:<p>Alternate Configuration A is optimized for forward observation and anti-infantry suppression rather than direct combat. A TAG laser designator allows the 'Mech to call in Arrow IV artillery strikes with precision, making the A configuration a devastating force multiplier when operating alongside artillery-equipped Starmates. Two anti-missile systems provide unusual defensive capability for a light 'Mech, while two machine guns, a flamer, and a pair of A-Pods create an effective screen against infantry and battle armor. The A configuration sacrifices virtually all anti-'Mech capability in exchange for exceptional support utility, making it highly dependent on its Star for protection against armored threats.</p>

history:<p>The Mist Lynx was developed by Clan Smoke Jaguar scientists during the early decades of the thirtieth century, emerging as a dedicated light scout designed to exploit OmniMech technology at the lightest practical weight class. The design quickly proved popular, and through Trials of Possession and political exchanges, the Mist Lynx spread to virtually every Clan's touman within a generation of its introduction.</p><p>During Operation REVIVAL in 3049, Draconis Combine forces encountered the Mist Lynx extensively across multiple invasion corridors. The design earned its Inner Sphere reporting name "Koshi" from DCMS intelligence analysts, a term reflecting the 'Mech's ability to inflict disproportionate damage through hit-and-run tactics. Clan Smoke Jaguar fielded the largest concentration of Mist Lynxes during the invasion, though the design appeared in nearly every invading Clan's order of battle.</p><p>The Annihilation of Clan Smoke Jaguar following Operation BULLDOG and the Great Refusal in 3060 disrupted primary production at the Huntress Production Facility Epsilon. Clans Ice Hellion and Steel Viper both took advantage of the SLDF's invasion of Huntress to trial for the right to manufacture the light OmniMech, bringing it back into production before the Wars of Reaving. The Steel Vipers secured ongoing production at the Arcadia BattleMech Plant CM-O3, while the Ice Hellions maintained output from Huntress.</p><p>The Wars of Reaving in 3070 brought further turmoil to Mist Lynx production lines. During the conflict, Steel Viper forces employed Mist Lynxes in rapid flanking actions during the seizure of Lum, where a Binary of the light OmniMechs outmaneuvered Snow Raven auxiliaries attempting to intervene. The subsequent destruction of Clan Steel Viper and the absorption of Clan Ice Hellion further redistributed production facilities among the surviving Clans.</p><p>During the ilClan era, the Mist Lynx continued to demonstrate its enduring tactical value. As Clan Wolf marched toward Terra, Mist Lynxes of the Ninth Wolf Guard Striker Cluster provided essential reconnaissance on Alula Australis, foiling multiple Republic headhunter attempts targeting senior Clan officers. The design's presence across centuries of conflict and political upheaval speaks to both its fundamental soundness and the widespread industrial capacity dedicated to its continued manufacture.</p>

manufacturer:Huntress Production Facility Epsilon, Arcadia BattleMech Plant CM-03, Manufacturing Plant SFF-AL1, Albion Armor Works Gamma, Marshall Light Assembly Station

primaryfactory:Huntress (Warrior Path), Arcadia (East), Alnabog (Chain Cluster), Albion (Indicass), Marshall (Queensland)

